cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.DB

This paper deals with privacy and machine learning, specifically the vulnerability of machine learning algorithms to membership inference attacks and the algorithmic fairness of these attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of differential privacy as a defense mechanism, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the impact of differential privacy on vulnerability disparity, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper uses real-world datasets, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases).
